            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is a scalar function in Microsoft SQL Server designed to evaluate and return a specific value based on the input parameters provided. Scalar functions return a single value, which can be used in queries wherever an expression is valid. This function is used to encapsulate business logic that determines the validity of a delivery in a production environment."
